The paper deals with neural architecture search (NAS) using reinforcement learning (RL) and explores a novel paradigm of non-stationary policy gradient (NPG) to efficiently approximate the full Pareto front in multi-objective NAS. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) which deals with the development of algorithms and models for machine learning. 

The paper also deals with computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) could be possible sub-categories. 

The paper also introduces a novel exploration scheme and a pre-trained shared model, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be possible sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of multiple conflicting objectives, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a possible sub-category.
